main event: A bright point of light, resembling the size of a star, was observed traveling steadily from N to S at an estimated speed of 1,500 mph for about 5 seconds before disappearing. No sound was heard during the sighting.
interesting points: The witness described the object as a bright point of light, steady, white in color, and about the size of a star, traveling at high speed without making any sound.
The object's speed and course led to the suggestion that it was a jet aircraft, offering a prosaic explanation for the sighting.
The witness had also reported seeing a group of 5 or 6 objects silently traveling in the past, indicating previous UFO encounters.
There was a mention of a photograph sent in with a report, but the content of the photograph is not described.
A witness from a UFO club called 'Civilization Identified' reported a sighting, raising questions about the credibility of the witness.
photographs: the report mentions photographs but the content is not described
